improve the $L^{\\infty}$\nversion of this result originally established in \\cite{IM2020}. By using an\nextension of the combinatorial idea from \\cite{IR03}, we prove that under the\n$L^{\\infty}$ hypothesis, $A$ is finite if $d \\not=1 \\mod 4$. If $d=1$ mod $4,\nA$ may be infinite, but if it is, then it must be a subset of a line.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 22 Jan 2023 15:48:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-24"}
